wdi2-SG.LAW.INDX.def: The index measures how laws and regulations affect women’s economic opportunity.  Overall scores are calculated by taking the average score of each of the eight areas (Going Places, Starting a Job, Getting Paid, Getting Married, Having Children, Running a Business, Managing Assets and Getting a Pension), with 100 representing the highest possible score.
wdi2-SG.LAW.INDX.name: Women Business and the Law Index Score
wdi2-SG.LAW.INDX.source: World Bank: Women, Business and the Law. https://wbl.worldbank.org/
